    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>A continuous ribbon or band of loose, untwisted fiber that is used to spin yarn. A sliver is created by carding or combing fiber and drawing it into parallel strips that are then ready for drawing, roving, or slubbing.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
